description: Permanently deletes a GeoMatchSet. You can't delete a GeoMatchSet if it's still used in any Rules or if it still includes any countries. If you just want to remove a GeoMatchSet from a Rule, use UpdateRule. To permanently delete a GeoMatchSet from AWS WAF, perform the following steps:   Update the GeoMatchSet to remove any countries. For more information, see UpdateGeoMatchSet.   Use GetChangeToken to get the change token that you provide in the ChangeToken parameter of a DeleteGeoMatchSet request.   Submit a DeleteGeoMatchSet request.
